<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 2:38PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Lamar County through
315 PM EDT...
At 238 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Aldora, or over
Barnesville, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Barnesville, Milner, Orchard Hill, Aldora, Redbone, Liberty Hill,
Goggins, Piedmont, Johnstonville and Chappel Mill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
